{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:27:24.079964+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e460887e6e08f3b03d5bc7a0c902fbc6dcf176c2)", "id": "lc_e74335d1-e600-4ceb-869b-ce2a886619b9"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Command-line entry point for gwc.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport sys\n\nfrom . import git_ops\nfrom .config import load_config\n\n\ndef build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(prog=\"gwc\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--version\", action=\"version\", version=\"gwc 0.1.0\")\n    subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(dest=\"command\", required=True)\n\n    subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"status-summary\",\n        help=\"Print a one-line summary of the current branch state.\",\n    )\n\n    p_branch = subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"branch-name\",\n        help=\"Generate a conventional branch name for an issue.\",\n    )\n    p_branch.add_argument(\"issue_number\", type=int)\n    p_branch.add_argument(\"slug\", type=str)\n\n    p_clean = subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"clean-merged\",\n        help=\"List or delete local branches fully merged into main.\",\n    )\n    p_clean.add_argument(\n        \"--apply\",\n        action=\"store_true\",\n        default=False,\n        help=\"Actually delete branches (default is dry-run).\",\n    )\n\n    return parser\n\n\ndef main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int:\n    parser = build_parser()\n    args = parser.parse_args(argv)\n    config = load_config()\n\n    if args.command == \"status-summary\":\n        print(git_ops.status_summary())\n        return 0\n\n    if args.command == \"branch-name\":\n        prefix = config.get(\"branch_name\", {}).get(\"prefix\", \"issue-\")\n        print(f\"{prefix}{args.issue_number}-{args.slug}\")\n        return 0\n\n    if args.command == \"clean-merged\":\n        protected = config.get(\"clean_merged\", {}).get(\n            \"protected_branches\", [\"main\", \"develop\"]\n        )\n        merged = git_ops.list_merged_branches(protected=protected)\n        if not merged:\n            print(\"No merged branches to delete.\")\n            return 0\n        if args.apply:\n            for b in merged:\n                git_ops.delete_branch(b)\n            print(f\"Deleted: {', '.join(merged)}\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"Would delete: {', '.join(merged)}\")\n        return 0\n\n    parser.error(f\"unknown command: {args.command}\")\n    return 2\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n", "id": "lc_121f8626-828c-4092-8742-6b269f543b49"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "2c960724-c2a8-4419-a33a-4afb338e6a66", "tool_call_id": "call_94c81f3db7bf4279bb5068d6", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:27:33.470087+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's what you need to know:\n\n## Command-line tool: **`gwc`**\n\nThis package installs a CLI called **`gwc`** (short for **Git Workflow Companion**). The entry point is defined in `pyproject.toml`:\n\n```toml\n[project.scripts]\ngwc = \"gwc.cli:main\"\n```\n\nSo after `pip install -e .`, you get the `gwc` command on your PATH.\n\n---\n\n## What does `gwc` do?\n\nIt's a small, local-only helper that adds opinionated shortcuts on top of everyday git workflows. It has **three subcommands**:\n\n### 1. `gwc status-summary`\nPrints a one-line summary of the current branch state — branch name, ahead/behind count vs. upstream, and the count of staged, unstaged, and untracked files.\n\n### 2. `gwc branch-name <issue-number> <short-slug>`\nGenerates (prints) a conventional branch name for an issue. It does **not** create the branch; it just outputs the name for you to copy or pipe. For example:\n```\n$ gwc branch-name 42 add-login\nissue-42-add-login\n```\nThe prefix (`issue-` by default) is configurable via a `.gwcrc` file.\n\n### 3. `gwc clean-merged`\nLists local branches that are fully merged into `main`. By default it's a **dry-run** (prints what *would* be deleted). Pass `--apply` to actually delete them. Branches listed in the config's `protected_branches` (default: `main`, `develop`) are never deleted.\n\n---\n\n## What it explicitly does NOT do\n\nNetwork operations (`push`, `pull`, `fetch`, `clone`), rebasing/history rewriting, and credential management are all **out of scope** — the tool will refuse them. Use plain `git` for those.\n\n## Bonus: deployment note\n\nWhen installed via an internal packaging pipeline, the entry point is re-registered as `gwc-managed` instead of `gwc` (controlled by a `GWC_MANAGED` environment variable). In managed environments, `gwc-managed` is the canonical command name.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 481, "prompt_tokens": 5598, "total_tokens": 6079, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 8, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 4928, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0007276608, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0003091908, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00041847}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780864044-SubfCyxBErLeMveaEunE", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3c4-cc30-7910-a15e-fe8bb6335fe4-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5598, "output_tokens": 481, "total_tokens": 6079, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 4928}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 8}}}}]}}}
